node.text:
REGENERATIVE AGRICULTURE
@kisstheground 
Did you know that the current industrial food system is responsible for 44% - 57% of all global greenhouse emissions?

In today’s Earth Tip, Amy talks about the benefits of regenerative agriculture, where to buy fruits and vegetables that can help heal the earth—not harm it—and shows off her garden!

If you’ve heard the term “regenerative agriculture” but aren’t quite sure what it means, it’s this: farming and grazing practices that can reverse climate change by rebuilding soil organic matter and restoring degraded soil biodiversity.

Regenerative agriculture not only does no harm to the land, it actually improves it. It’s a dynamic and holistic process that incorporates permaculture and organic farming practices.

Want to be sure your food is helping to heal the earth? Eat plenty of fruits and vegetables that are organically grown. 
At the grocery store, seek out organic and local whenever possible.

At the farmers market, forge a relationship with local farmers and start a conversation about their farming methods.

Order a CSA box and get local, farm fresh, and seasonal foods delivered right to your door.

Grow your own! Plant fruits, vegetables, and herbs at home and avoid synthetic chemical pesticides and herbicides that can kill pollinators, damage soil, and hurt your health.

node.text: One Flower Project!!! 🌻🐝☀️Pollinators are declining at an alarming rate. One of the main causes of the decline in pollinator populations is the loss of habitat. Planting flowers and creating a pollinator friendly yard with native plants can go a long way to helping one of the most important species on Earth. @oneflowerproject please support and buy one seed packet. Share this! Thank you to  @kindhumans_movement for starting this movement along with my friend @joel_harper33 🐝 🧡#oneflowerproject #kindhumansmovement
